# Documentation Maintenance

- Update `.agents/30-records/logs/` at the end of each development session
- Follow `AGENTS.md` and `.agents/README.md` for the current agent record workflow
- Update `docs/troubleshooting-pitfalls.md` only when a new human-facing failure mode or durable fix pattern should be preserved for users
- Keep `docs/troubleshooting-pitfalls.md` in its existing topic structure when it needs an update
- Add troubleshooting entries under the closest `##` topic section
- Use the exact field order `Problem` `Cause` `Solution`
- Merge duplicate troubleshooting entries instead of appending near copies
- Update `README.md` when setup commands architecture or user visible behavior changes
- Update `docs/PROJECT_STATUS.md` when the project baseline changes in a meaningful way
